# Rangers — Master Project Context

## Identity
- **Project**: Rangers — shared dashboard platform
- **Users**: ~6 friends building and sharing widgets, scrapers, market watchers, automation tools
- **Architecture**: Widget-based dashboard with shared builds, per-user customization
- **Languages**: JavaScript (frontend, widgets, tooling) + Python (scrapers, automation, data processing)

## Core Principles
1. **Composability**: Every tool/widget must be self-contained and composable into any dashboard layout
2. **Share-first**: All builds are shareable by default — widgets, tools, scrapers can be pulled into any member's dashboard
3. **Dual-language**: JS for frontend/interactive widgets, Python for backend automation/data — both are first-class
4. **Fun-first**: This is a creative playground — prioritize cool functionality and fast iteration over enterprise patterns
5. **Multi-user**: Each user has their own dashboard state, but can browse and import each other's widgets

## File Organization
- `/src/widgets/` — Individual widget modules (JS)
- `/src/scrapers/` — Python scrapers and data collectors
- `/src/automation/` — Python automation tools
- `/src/dashboard/` — Dashboard framework and layout engine
- `/src/shared/` — Shared utilities used by both JS and Python
- `/src/api/` — API layer connecting frontend to Python backends
- `/config/` — Project configuration and shared facts
- `/tests/` — Test files (both JS and Python)
- `/scripts/` — Build, deploy, and utility scripts
- `/docs/` — Documentation

## Design Direction
- Dark theme by default (developer/hacker aesthetic)
- Widget cards with clean borders, grid-based layout
- Draggable/resizable widget placement
- Each user gets their own color accent for attribution
- Minimal chrome — maximize widget content area

## Hard Rules
- R1: Every widget must export a standard interface (render, configure, destroy)
- R2: No widget may directly access another widget's state — use the shared event bus
- R3: Python tools must expose a JSON API endpoint for the JS frontend to consume
- R4: All user data must be scoped by user ID — no cross-user data leaks
- R5: Secrets go in .env.local only — never in code, never committed
- R6: Widget configs are JSON — no YAML, no TOML for widget definitions
- R7: Every scraper must have a rate-limit configuration
- R8: All market watchers must cache data — don't hit external APIs on every render
